er’."]}]},{"name":"Donal","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Earlier  Domhnall , from Old Celtic <i>dubno</i> ‘world’ + <i>val</i> ‘rule’."],"variants":[{"name":"Donall","meanings":["Earlier  Domhnall , from Old Celtic <i>dubno</i> ‘world’ + <i>val</i> ‘rule’."]}]},{"name":"Glas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Blasius</i>, probably from <i>blaesus</i> ‘lisping’.  See  <b>Blaise</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vlasi","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Blasius</i>, probably from <i>blaesus</i> ‘lisping’.  See  <b>Blaise</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Donal Glas MacCarthy Reagh 5th pince of carbery was born in 1340, in Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Ireland, his father, Donald Glas I Maccarthy, was 21 and his mother, Julia O'Cromin, was 11. He had at least 5 sons with Joanna Margaret Fitz Maurice. He died in 1414, in Tralee, County Kerry, Ireland, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1340–1414":"1340–1414","1384–1418":"1384–1418","1410–1473":"1410–1473","1411–Male":"1411–Surnud","1413–1442":"1413–1442","1414–Male":"1414–Surnud","1415–1432":"1415–1432","1320–1366":"1320–1366","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1330":"1330","1473":"1473","1340":"1340","1384":"1384","1415":"1415","1414":"1414","1413":"1413","1411":"1411","1366":"1366","1410":"1410","1432":"1432","1442":"1442","about 1414":"umbes 1414","1320":"1320","1418":"1418","Tralee, Kerry, Ireland":"Tralee, County Kerry, Iirimaa","Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Ireland":"Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Cork, County Cork, Ireland":"Cork, County Cork, Iirimaa","Carbery, Ireland":"Carbury, County Kildare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1340–1414":"1340–1414","1384–1418":"1384–1418","1410–1473":"1410–1473","1411–Male":"1411–Kuollut","1413–1442":"1413–1442","1414–Male":"1414–Kuollut","1415–1432":"1415–1432","1320–136